Yes, this is completely what it is.  A lot of people have opinions on matters, and they aren't sure why they have them.  ND 3 is one of them.  Everyone spouts &quot;Get ND3! Get ND3!  It's the most important AA for EVERYONE!&quot; <br>
<br>
BULLSHIT.<br>
<br>
When I hit 60, the majority of my XP time was spent with my shaman and when I did group, the main healer was a druid.  This was before Tunare's Renewal and Kragg's mending were in the game.  I didn't raid, my guild hadn't started yet and I hate any guild led by someone else.  Was ND3 the correct choice for me?  Absolutely not.  ND 3 wouldn't have done jack or crap to speed up the rate that I grinded AA's.  CA and CS however, affected me greatly.  When your best heal only heals 1200 of your HP over 24 seconds, whether you have 3000 or 3300 is completely irrelevant.  I spent most of my time berserk anyway, and the only time i was at full HP was when I started.  Durability would have been a waste for me...just something to increase my virtual penis size by looking at a big number.<br>
<br>
If you're not grouping with a cleric consistently, not raiding, and have to depend on something like Kragg's mending and Torpor for your heals, then yes..ND 3 is useless.  Get CA3 first and you'll be much better off because your healer will spend less time healing you.<br>
<br>
